            "id": "4542826",
            "title": "NextEra Energy reports mixed Q4 results; reaffirms FY26 outlook",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>NextEra Energy <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20376975-nextera-energy-fourth-quarter-and-full-year-2025-financial-results-available-on-companys\">press release</a>  (NEE): Q4  Non-GAAP EPS of $0.54 <font color=\"green\"> beats by $0.01</font>.</li>\n<li>Revenue of $6.5B (+20.6% Y/Y) <font color=\"red\"> misses by $290M</font>.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Outlook</strong> NextEra Energy's long-term financial expectations remain unchanged from what the company shared at the investor conference last December. NextEra Energy continues to expect 2026 adjusted earnings per share to be in the range of $3.92 to $4.02 <strong>vs. consensus of $4.01</strong>. NextEra Energy also continues to expect a compound annual growth rate in adjusted earnings per share of 8%+ annually through 2032 and is targeting the same from 2032 through 2035, all off the 2025 base of $3.71 adjusted earnings per share. NextEra Energy also continues to expect to grow its dividends per share at a roughly 10% rate per year through 2026, off a 2024 base, and 6% per year from year-end 2026 through 2028.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
