            "id": "4542812",
            "title": "Stock index futures mixed as Trump announces more tariffs",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\" data-id=\"fc3b879f-12be-4ee0-9d49-e9f05f982206\" data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\"><span data-ai=\"\">Stock index futures were mixed before the bell, recovering ground after initial volatility driven by geopolitical trade tensions.</span></p>\n<p data-id=\"dd115906-7742-4d01-b928-9bfc7831a594\"><span data-ai=\"\">Nasdaq 100 futures (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US100:IND\" title=\"NASDAQ 100 Futures\">US100:IND</a>) led the advance, rising +0.86%, while S&amp;P 500 futures (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/SPX\" title=\"S&amp;P 500 Futures\">SPX</a></span>) edged higher by +0.42%. Dow futures (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/INDU\" title=\"Dow Jones Futures\">INDU</a></span>) slipped -0.18%. The mixed movement occurred as investors digested a tariff threat directed at South Korean imports.</span></p>\n<p data-id=\"f3385f93-bf2d-4e53-a56e-303792f458c5\"><span data-ai=\"\">U.S. Treasury yields moved marginally higher on the long end of the curve. The 30-year yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US30Y\" title=\"United States 30-Year Bond Yield\">US30Y</a>) advanced 1 basis point to 4.81%, and the 10-year yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US10Y\" title=\"United States 10-Year Bond Yield\">US10Y</a>) rose 0.8 basis points to 4.23%. Meanwhile, the short-end 2-year yield (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/US2Y\" title=\"United States 2-Year Bond Yield\">US2Y</a>) slipped marginally by 0.2 basis points to 3.60%.</span></p>\n<p data-id=\"5909875b-7405-458c-b444-a7224ed8bf1f\"><span data-ai=\"\">UBS chief economist Paul Donovan noted the initial negative market response to President Donald Trump’s threatened 25% tariff on South Korean imports, but observed markets recovered because “the absence of responsible officials reacting to the post undermines the credibility of the post.”</span></p>\n<p data-id=\"9bccf020-c49b-4ef0-9be4-24806135e80a\"><span data-ai=\"\">Top gainers in premarket trading included Micron Technology (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/MU\" title=\"Micron Technology, Inc.\">MU</a>) +4.60%, General Motors Company (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/GM\" title=\"General Motors Company\">GM</a>) +4.57%, and Intel Corporation (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/INTC\" title=\"Intel Corporation\">INTC</a>) +3.39%. Decliners included Humana Inc. (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/HUM\" title=\"Humana Inc.\">HUM</a>) -15.53%, UnitedHealth Group Incorporated (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UNH\" title=\"UnitedHealth Group Incorporated\">UNH</a>) -15.25%, and CVS Health Corporation (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CVS\" title=\"CVS Health Corporation\">CVS</a>) -12.96%.</span></p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
